This paper deals with reasoning and explanation facilities for logic-based applications, specifically in the context of Description Logics. This makes it highly likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper focuses on query answering and ABox reasoning, which are relevant topics in the sub-categories of Databases (cs.DB) and Computation and Language (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also deals with computational complexity, which is a topic in the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
